description: Collects : Deadpool (1997) # 32 - Wolverine (2003) # 34,35
name: Target: Nick Fury!

description:
Daken’s battle with the X-Men explodes into a brutal frenzy – can Wolverine save both his son and his teammates?!

By Daniel Way and Doug Braithwaite.

Also: Norman Osborn stole some vital info from Deadpool, which resulted in loss of face – and earnings! Now the Merc with the Mouth wants his money back, and he’s going to blast his way through the all-new Thunderbolts to get it!

By Daniel Way and Paco Medina.

Includes material reprinted from Wolverine: Origins #35, Deadpool #8 and Thunderbolts #130.

Earth’s new Sorcerer Supreme must be chosen! Will Doctor Strange and the Secret Avengers find him before the dread Dormammu?!

Also: Norman Osborn grapples with the Sentry’s madness, and the Dark Avengers and Doctor Doom clash with the sinister Morgana Le Fey!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Avengers #3-4 and New Avengers #51.
name: Who Will Be The Sorcerer Supreme?

description:
No more secrets. No more lies. With Menace unmasked, the whole story of who he is and how he came to be is finally revealed and it promises to shake Peter Parker’s world to its foundation.

Also, Spidey's loved ones are in danger, but to save them he'll have to face thirty of his deadliest foes. Meanwhile, Carlie Cooper and Vin Gonzales are in deeper trouble than they thought and Harry Osborn and Lily Hollister face the election results.

Plus, classic adventure, as the web-slinger encounters the Humbug!

Story and art by Marc Guggenheim, John Romita Jr, David Michelinie and Todd McFarlane!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #577 and Amazing Spider-Man #308! 76 pages!
name: Menace Revealed!

description: Cable has taken over the New Mutants and molded them into a precision strike force! With new members Shatterstar, Warpath, Domino, Siryn and Feral, the group is ready to face any threat, and is determined to shut down Stryfe and his Mutant Liberation Front once and for all! And when the Juggernaut and Black Tom take a building full of hostages, X-Force needs Spider-Man’s help to stop them! Featuring the first appearance of Deadpool! Collecting NEW MUTANTS #98-100, X-FORCE #1-4 & SPIDER-MAN #16.
name: X-Force : A Force To Be Reckoned With HC

name: Zombies vs. Transformers; Zombies vs. Star Trek; Zombies vs. G.I. Joe; Zombies vs. Ghostbusters

description: In the politics, struggles, and battles that lead to the birth of a nation, sometimes even good people must die at the hands of allies. And now it's down to only a few warlords of Edo-era Japan. History already tells the story of the victor, but the real guts of Path of the Assassin lie in the characters behind the scenes--the ninja warriors doing the dirty work. Theirs is a story of families and war and intrigue, only far more mysterious and untold.
name: Hateful Burden

description:
Assassins have been cast as the sensual and shadowy villains throughout history, but their exploits have never been so fully realized as they are within the pages of Path of the Assassin. From the most intense sword fight, to a silent poisoning, no job has been too much for the infamous Hattori Hanzo. Now, the stage is set for Tokugawa Ieyasu's destiny to be fulfilled, and with Hanzo watching his back, can anything stop him from uniting Japan?

For the past fourteen volumes Hanzo's long walk down the tightrope of political intrigue and human melodrama has been bloody, dramatic, and awe inspiring. Every page filled with the densely researched and poignant delivery you've come to expect from the godfathers of samurai manga. Lone Wolf and Cub creators Kazuo Koike and Goseki Kojima, experts of gekiga samurai manga, deliver the penultimate volume of Path of the Assassin.
name: Bad Blood

description: Poor Ghost. First she thinks she's dead, then she finds out she's not, but she's still stuck being a ghost. Worse, she seems to have a knack for finding the strangest creatures the dark underbelly of Arcadia has to offer. Two strange encounters are presented here: Ghost's confrontation with the insectoid horror known as "Mayfly," and her uncovering of demonic "Secrets" reprinted from its serialization in Diamond Previews. Twice as many pages, twice as much adventure!
name: Scary Monsters

description: The out-of-this-world conclusion to “Mickey Mouse and the Orbiting Nightmare” by modern Mickey master Casty! With chaos on the space palace Olympus reaching a fever pitch, Mickey must confront a villain from his past who seeks to create the ultimate weapon. Only with help from an unexpected visitor can Mickey hope to prevail and return to Earth!
name: Mickey Mouse and the Orbiting Nightmare part 2; Tidy Friday

description: The ongoing manga adaptation of the hit anime series continues. Get ready for buxom babes, beastmen, and giant mechs as only GAINAX can provide them!
name: Vol. 4

description:
Madelyne Pryor assembles a team of lethal ladies with a dark plan in mind! Meanwhile, Charles Xavier and Gambit head for Australia in search of Rogue, but an old enemy has found her first! The ghosts of the X-Men’s past have become real – and deadly!

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny #508 and X-Men Legacy #220-221.
name: The Fate of Rogue!

description:
Think you've got problems? Meet the patients in Dr. Burton's Wednesday--afternoon support group. Violet carries a jar full of demons. Roger can read minds. Akiko talks with her dead parents through the bathroom mirror. Joe is an exorcist. Brian is pyrokinetic. And then, of course, there's Charles.

They've been thrown together by the luck of the draw, stuck with supernatural powers they don't want and can't control. But when something begins to pick them off one by one, the surviving members of the Wednesday Conspiracy find themselves the last, reluctant line of defense between the reincarnation of an ancient evil and the fate of the world.

In the tradition of the uber-successful Ultimate Spider-Man #100 Project, the Hero Initiative pops its claws! All of Hero's original covers to Marvel Comics' Wolverine: Weapon X #1 are on display in this great book, with art by J. Scott Campbell, John Cassaday, Frank Cho, Ron Garney, Dale Keown, John Romita Sr. and more!

Warlord's Gun of Peace

The American situation was perilous! The supply train was completely cut off-- surrounded on all sides-- by overwhelming forces of howling communists lusting for their blood and their supplies! Sooner or later, the U.N. forces were bound to run out of ammunition! Sooner or later, the screeching red fanatics would break through their thin line of defense! But there was no thought of giving up...

Not the Bluffing Kind

The ancient walled town on Sinpo was one of the most vital hilltop bastions in the entire U.N. line --- and that was why major Paul Cummings had been chosen to command the town's defenses. The major had built up a brilliant reputation in battle, but only a few of his aides knew that he always succeeded because he never took any chances and never bluffed. But the day finally came when Cummings found out that it was a fatal mistake not to bluff...!

The Last Patrol

He was forty, too old, according to rear echelon brass, to hold down the command of a combat engineer company. So they were going to put him in cold storage, give him a desk job, and make a paper soldier of him. But captain Jack Beatty could not be retired from active duty that easily...

Bullet Baptism (Text Only Story)

Abandon Tank!

Korea had become the testing ground for the most horribly destructive weapons yet devised by the human mind. As the tide of battle swung against them, the Reds threw off the wraps on their latest blitz machine to stop the U.N. Forces cold in their tracks...

name: Double Trouble
Yuck!
Monster School Invasions
Captain Jack's best moments

description: A collection of stories with additional artwork.
name: Ghost Stories

description:
Peter Kolinsky was among the world's foremost experts on rare books, with a top position at a prestigious auction house, until black marketers took an interest in him. Since narrowly avoiding jail time, Peter's lived a lonely life in a tiny apartment, with a menial job he hates.

Things look like they might turn around when, looking for a late-night snack, Peter wanders into a café and meets Angela. She shows him the Archives, where books currently being written are somehow on the shelves. It's a book-lover's dream until the black marketer who ruined Peter's life returns with a grudge. On the run, will Peter find salvation in the Archives, or further ruin?

A man who may or may not be what he claims, goes insane in a library of unwritten books that may or may not exist.
name: Insomnia Café
Warning!
Look Out ! Who's this Monster?
Upgrade Now!
Watch Out!
Top 10 Sonic Scenes
Aargh!
Who's Back!

Doctor Light is missing, and her former Justice League teammates intend to find the man responsible and make him pay. But before they do that, they'll have to get past his Shadow Cabinet of powerful superbeings who have sworn to "Save humanity from itself." 
 
Justice League of America issues 27, 28, 30-34.
name: When Worlds Collide

volume.name: Justice League of America: When Worlds Collide

description:
She's the beautiful daughter of a brilliant scientist. He's a super-intelligent gorilla from another dimension. Together they're Monkeyman & O'Brien -- two rays of hope in a world gone mad! Join Art Adams for 32 pages of non-stop, eye-popping action in this science-fiction adventure which originally appeared in Mike Mignola's Hellboy: Seed of Destruction.

The Origin of Monkeyman & O'Brien.
name: Who are Monkeyman & O'Brien?

description:
P. Craig Russell's stunning saga of the Norse gods and heroes nears its conclusion with Gotterdammerung: The Twilight of the Gods, the final arc in The Ring of the Nibelung series. The unique cast of characters -- gods, heroes, and monsters -- are brought together by their various schemes and betrayals, leading to the explosive climax. Siegfried gives his Ring of the Nibelung to his beloved Valkyrie and goes out into the world, setting events in motion to bring the curtain down on the heavens and earth.

The Ring of the Nibelung Book Four: Gotterdammerung - The Twilight of the Gods
name: Chapter One: The Rope of Fate

volume.name: The Ring of the Nibelung: Gotterdammerung (Book Four)

name: Watch Out!

description:
Mankind's greatest hero, Siegfried, is wooed by love and lust to make a pledge which will condemn his beloved Valkyrie and bring the attention of Wotan. Violence and ill-conceived marriages go hand in hand as the magical Ring is once again exchanged. There is only one last chance to avoid the death of man and gods alike. P. Craig Russell's graceful adaptation of the Germanic opera cycle continues on its journey of innocence, greed, and the glistening beauty of a time when Gods walked the earth.

The Ring of the Nibelung Book Four: Gotterdammerung - The Twilight of the Gods
name: Chapter One: Blood for Blood

volume.name: The Ring of the Nibelung: Gotterdammerung (Book Four)

description:
Siegfried hands Brunhildé off as a bride to another man, but the Valkyrie won't be so easily discarded. The entire clan of the Gibichung are up in arms over accusations of rape and infidelity, as different players conspire to get possession of the ring. The fate of the gods is in the hands of men, for once.

The Ring of the Nibelung Book Four: Gotterdammerung - The Twilight of the Gods
name: Chapter Two: Double Blind

volume.name: The Ring of the Nibelung: Gotterdammerung (Book Four)

description:
The ultimate price is finally paid for the Ring and the Rhinegold. All betrayals made in the name of love or the name of greed come full circle as all in heaven and earth pay for their roles in Wagner's epic tragedy. P. Craig Russell wraps up his masterpiece, the fourteen-issue Ring of the Nibelung series, with this double-sized issue, presenting the most brilliantly realized portrait of the end of the world ever drawn.

The Ring of the Nibelung Book Four: Gotterdammerung - The Twilight of the Gods
name: Chapter Three: Revenge, Redemption, & the Return of the King

volume.name: The Ring of the Nibelung: Gotterdammerung (Book Four)
